Description.SourceString: The foundation of a mysterious tower.
A half-built tower that holds secrets in its cold walls.
An enigmatic tower that stands out from the barren landscape.
A tower bursting with unharnessed possibility.
A mock-up of a logo that a Sakura 7 gang member carved into a table.
A keychain from the forum Claudette moderated.

It’s your wacky elephant pal as a plush toy! He can’t wait to play in your red puddles! 

Design inspired by kangyaku.
Yui’s favorite speed? Faster.
A rare flower that grows in Cuba and Florida. Claudette’s favorite.
The figure of a Japanese ogre. It’s smiling viciously.
Everything Sally held dear was taken away.
An artifact once prevalent in The Entity’s realm, it vanished quite suddenly.
A treat made by pouring hot maple sap onto snow. Part of French-Canadian culture, where it’s known as tire d'érable.
The hand of someone who succumbed to the cold night.
An oxymoron known as frozen hot cocoa.
A relic from the Observer’s tower. Some say these roses once held powerful sway over The Entity’s realm.
A flag marking the end of a race, its significance is diminished in a realm where endings are ambiguous.
A knife-shaped icicle. May be effective at killing snowmen.
A tattoo Kazan stripped from a man’s skin, deeming him unworthy of wearing such a noble symbol.
A relic from the halls of Crotus Prenn Asylum.
It may have been beautiful once, but such things are the first to break in this realm.
A souped-up streetbike that Yui rode to many victories on.
Sally’s wedding ring. Only a piece of that woman remained.
She doubted the work she performed but had little else remaining.
The death of her husband tore her soul apart.
She was drifting towards a monstrous act as she succumbed to the darkness.
She understood her purpose now. And it was to cleanse.
The dream felt real. And in it, she was utterly destroyed.
She felt empty after witnessing the horrible crash of her friend.
There was a thought she couldn’t purge from her mind: Revenge.
What does it matter if you gain the world if you lose your humanity?
She realized some things are more important than first place.
A strong and reliable beast with an indomitable will.
A beacon of hope in a realm of suffering and despair.
